1
00:01:11,800 --> 00:01:12,440
Xu Xiao.

2
00:01:14,480 --> 00:01:15,010
Xiaocen.

3
00:01:16,320 --> 00:01:17,920
Aren't you going back today?

4
00:01:18,280 --> 00:01:19,210
I'm not leaving.

5
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:24,930
Not leaving?

6
00:01:26,880 --> 00:01:27,840
You told me

7
00:01:28,440 --> 00:01:29,720
to follow my heart.

8
00:01:32,440 --> 00:01:34,300
I thought about it for a long time.

9
00:01:34,560 --> 00:01:35,960
I used to be too cowardly.

10
00:01:36,920 --> 00:01:39,780
I was afraid to bear the consequences of my choices.

11
00:01:40,039 --> 00:01:40,800
So before,

12
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:43,000
my family always made decisions for me.

13
00:01:46,360 --> 00:01:47,000
But now,

14
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:49,330
I have the courage to choose my own future,

15
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:51,890
and the courage to bear the consequences.

16
00:01:55,600 --> 00:01:56,660
So I'm going to stay

17
00:01:57,280 --> 00:01:58,600
and do what I like to do.

18
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:00,840
With you.

19
00:02:17,200 --> 00:02:17,800
So

20
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:20,800
you're not changing your major?

21
00:02:22,040 --> 00:02:23,040
And this holiday,

22
00:02:23,040 --> 00:02:24,440
I'll stay in Jingdezhen.

23
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:31,120
What's wrong?

24
00:02:31,640 --> 00:02:32,600
This holiday,

25
00:02:34,280 --> 00:02:35,680
I won't be in Jingdezhen.

26
00:02:37,280 --> 00:02:37,920
Why?

27
00:02:41,320 --> 00:02:42,040
Well,

28
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:43,740
it's the holidays.

29
00:02:43,960 --> 00:02:45,800
I saw there were fewer people on the court,

30
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:47,730
so I decided to stretch my muscles.

31
00:02:49,079 --> 00:02:51,360
And I ran into an old classmate of mine.

32
00:02:51,560 --> 00:02:53,020
He refused to admit defeat

33
00:02:53,360 --> 00:02:55,560
and insisted on playing one-on-one with me.

34
00:02:55,560 --> 00:02:56,400
So we played.

35
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:57,520
For over a dozen rounds,

36
00:02:57,520 --> 00:02:59,320
he couldn't defend a single one.

37
00:02:59,520 --> 00:03:00,800
As a result, extreme joy turned to sorrow,

38
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:02,330
and I got injured in combat.

39
00:03:03,880 --> 00:03:04,740
Never mind him.

40
00:03:05,720 --> 00:03:06,920
Fortunately, my wife

41
00:03:07,200 --> 00:03:08,000
isn't at home.

42
00:03:09,040 --> 00:03:10,500
Let me tell you something.

43
00:03:10,680 --> 00:03:11,120
Go ahead.

44
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:12,920
So, an old friend of mine

45
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:15,060
asked me a long time ago

46
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:17,480
to restore a batch of porcelain for him.

47
00:03:18,040 --> 00:03:19,079
I promised him.

48
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:21,890
I think you can complete this task.

49
00:03:22,280 --> 00:03:24,160
It's just that the place is a bit far.

50
00:03:24,160 --> 00:03:24,680
Where?

51
00:03:25,720 --> 00:03:26,400
Malaysia.

52
00:03:29,040 --> 00:03:30,240
I wanted to give you some time

53
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:31,240
to think it over.

54
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:34,160
So I accepted Mr. Yue's commission.

55
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:36,930
I didn't expect you to stay.

56
00:03:41,040 --> 00:03:41,800
It's okay.

57
00:03:44,280 --> 00:03:45,280
I'll wait for you.

58
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:20,560
Hello.

59
00:04:20,880 --> 00:04:21,279
Hello.

60
00:04:21,440 --> 00:04:22,500
You must be Xu Xiao.

61
00:04:22,840 --> 00:04:24,120
I'm Mr. Zeng's grandson.

62
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:24,920
My name is Zeng Yi.

63
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:26,180
You can call me Justin.

64
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:27,400
Welcome to Malaysia.

65
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:28,840
Let me help you with your luggage.

66
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:29,440
No thanks.

67
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:30,370
I can manage.

68
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:30,730
Okay.

69
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:34,840
This way.

70
00:04:34,840 --> 00:04:35,200
Okay.

71
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:42,570
Grandpa, the guest is here.

72
00:04:43,640 --> 00:04:44,240
After you.

73
00:04:47,440 --> 00:04:48,000
Mr. Zeng.

74
00:04:48,680 --> 00:04:49,280
Hello.

75
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:51,200
You must be Mr. Yue's student.

76
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:52,240
I am Zeng Yuren.

77
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:53,680
Nice to meet you.

78
00:04:54,200 --> 00:04:54,860
I am Xu Xiao.

79
00:04:55,159 --> 00:04:56,090
Nice to meet you.

80
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:04,560
Xiaocen, I've arrived in Malaysia.

81
00:05:05,640 --> 00:05:06,640
You must be tired.

82
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:07,980
How do you feel?

83
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:09,880
Not bad. Pretty good.

84
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:13,400
Where are you now?

85
00:05:14,560 --> 00:05:15,600
I'm at Mr. Zeng's house.

86
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:18,360
What kind of person is Mr. Zeng?

87
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:22,560
He seems to be a Malaysian-Chinese entrepreneur.

88
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:26,680
Then what kind of

89
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:28,320
porcelain does he want you to restore?

90
00:05:28,320 --> 00:05:29,250
I'm not sure yet.

91
00:05:29,960 --> 00:05:32,120
He doesn't seem to trust me much.

92
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:35,600
I believe you can do it.

93
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:39,640
Well,

94
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:41,440
it's quite late now.

95
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:43,690
Get some early rest.

96
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:45,000
Let's talk tomorrow.

97
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:46,520
Okay.

98
00:05:47,880 --> 00:05:48,280
Bye.

99
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:49,960
Bye.

100
00:05:57,840 --> 00:05:58,720
Malaysia.

101
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:02,440
Mr. Yue recommended him to go to Malaysia

102
00:06:02,440 --> 00:06:03,640
to help an overseas Chinese entrepreneur

103
00:06:03,640 --> 00:06:04,960
complete the restoration work.

104
00:06:04,960 --> 00:06:06,760
So you stayed in Jingdezhen

105
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:08,180
and he went abroad.

106
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:10,490
When will he be back?

107
00:06:11,720 --> 00:06:14,180
He'll probably be there the whole vacation.

108
00:06:15,440 --> 00:06:16,160
Yuexin.

109
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:17,720
I really envy you.

110
00:06:18,280 --> 00:06:20,000
You get to do your vacation part-time job

111
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:21,640
and work with Qi Yi.

112
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:25,770
Xiaocen.

113
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:27,320
I think

114
00:06:27,840 --> 00:06:29,200
Xu Xiao didn't just go to Malaysia

115
00:06:29,200 --> 00:06:30,800
to restore cultural relics.

116
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:31,600
Look.

117
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:34,740
I saw this project before.

118
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:36,840
This overseas Chinese is a board member

119
00:06:36,840 --> 00:06:38,640
of a top university in Malaysia.

120
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:39,840
Their school and ours

121
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:41,600
have a year-round exchange student program.

122
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:42,659
Exchange student?

123
00:06:43,080 --> 00:06:44,920
They provide full scholarships

124
00:06:45,440 --> 00:06:46,040
and also

125
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:48,280
opportunities to participate in national cultural relic restoration.

126
00:06:48,280 --> 00:06:49,840
A lot of people are competing for this.

127
00:06:49,840 --> 00:06:52,440
Mr. Yue just wants to send Xu Xiao

128
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:54,240
there as an exchange student.

129
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:55,640
Is this an interview too?

130
00:06:56,280 --> 00:06:56,960
Probably.

131
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:05,530
Sorry, Xiaocen.

132
00:07:06,080 --> 00:07:07,340
I've been busy all day,

133
00:07:07,440 --> 00:07:08,960
so I'm just calling you back now.

134
00:07:08,960 --> 00:07:09,640
It's fine.

135
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:12,720
How was your day?

136
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:14,480
I'm currently staying at

137
00:07:14,480 --> 00:07:16,240
Mr. Yue's overseas Chinese friend's place.

138
00:07:16,240 --> 00:07:19,100
At Mr. Zeng's, the one who accepted the commission.

139
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:21,640
They are restoring a batch of Ming Dynasty porcelain this time.

140
00:07:21,640 --> 00:07:22,720
They are all very precious.

141
00:07:22,720 --> 00:07:24,450
It's hard to see them back home.

142
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:25,800
Really?

143
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:28,680
Because they were salvaged from the seabed,

144
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:30,140
they are highly corroded.

145
00:07:30,320 --> 00:07:31,560
I need to desalinate them

146
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:33,020
and restore their colors.

147
00:07:34,840 --> 00:07:36,360
Can you fix them?

148
00:07:37,080 --> 00:07:37,920
Of course.

149
00:07:38,440 --> 00:07:40,360
Even though it's just me doing this,

150
00:07:40,360 --> 00:07:41,480
and the workload is a bit heavy,

151
00:07:41,480 --> 00:07:43,210
a college student will help me.

152
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,460
A student from over there?

153
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:46,000
Yes.

154
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:49,360
Someone studying restoration at a local university.

155
00:07:49,360 --> 00:07:50,360
He is also a student of

156
00:07:50,360 --> 00:07:53,490
the Cultural Relics Conservation major at this school.

157
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:56,440
How is the university there?

158
00:07:56,640 --> 00:07:57,760
It's very good.

159
00:07:57,920 --> 00:08:00,050
It's the best university in Malaysia.

160
00:08:00,840 --> 00:08:03,160
Their Cultural Relics Conservation major is also very good.

161
00:08:03,160 --> 00:08:05,360
The restoration courses are very professional,

162
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:07,520
and their equipment is even better than our school's.

163
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:08,440
So,

164
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:11,850
you also like that school a lot.

165
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:13,840
I like it a lot.

166
00:08:14,080 --> 00:08:14,680
Oh, right.

167
00:08:15,080 --> 00:08:16,320
After this batch of porcelain is restored,

168
00:08:16,320 --> 00:08:18,600
they will be exhibited in the school's Chinese Museum.

169
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:19,280
When the time comes,

170
00:08:19,280 --> 00:08:21,000
Mr. Zeng will take us to see

171
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:23,000
the results of our hard work.

172
00:08:24,360 --> 00:08:25,080
Is that so?

173
00:08:26,360 --> 00:08:28,160
Mr. Zeng is a director of this school.

174
00:08:28,160 --> 00:08:29,490
He's highly respected.

175
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:30,880
Do you

176
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:34,840
have anything else to tell me?

177
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:36,240
Nothing else.

178
00:08:36,880 --> 00:08:38,809
It's basically the same every day.

179
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:44,400
What's wrong?

180
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:46,320
I'm fine.

181
00:08:47,640 --> 00:08:48,280
I'm fine.

182
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:51,800
Are you going to rest?

183
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:53,280
It's getting late.

184
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:55,840
I still need to gather some

185
00:08:55,840 --> 00:08:56,960
materials for tomorrow's restoration.

186
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:58,360
I'll need them tomorrow.

187
00:08:59,040 --> 00:09:00,040
I'll go rest then.

188
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,400
I'll hang up then.

189
00:09:14,960 --> 00:09:15,640
Xiaocen,

190
00:09:16,480 --> 00:09:18,160
hasn't Xu Xiao told you

191
00:09:18,480 --> 00:09:21,080
that he might go abroad as an exchange student?

192
00:09:23,840 --> 00:09:27,040
He might be busy recently,

193
00:09:28,040 --> 00:09:29,680
working on the restoration.

194
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:31,080
I think

195
00:09:31,440 --> 00:09:33,500
he's having too much fun in Malaysia.

196
00:09:33,680 --> 00:09:35,240
You two will be apart for two years, and he doesn't even care.

197
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:36,080
Yan Xue,

198
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:38,440
Xu Xiao hasn't decided to go abroad yet.

199
00:09:39,320 --> 00:09:41,360
Maybe Xu Xiao has his own plans.

200
00:09:41,680 --> 00:09:44,200
He might want to discuss it with Xiaocen after coming back.

201
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:45,880
If he's decided not to study abroad,

202
00:09:45,880 --> 00:09:47,340
why doesn't he just say it?

203
00:09:47,360 --> 00:09:50,080
There's definitely a problem with him hiding it like this.

204
00:09:50,080 --> 00:09:52,320
If Xu Xiao has such a good opportunity,

205
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:55,720
I think he should take it.

206
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:58,520
Xiaocen,

207
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:00,260
don't always think of others.

208
00:10:00,480 --> 00:10:02,160
If you really want him to stay,

209
00:10:02,280 --> 00:10:04,000
just tell him directly.

210
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:09,680
I think it's Xu Xiao's own decision.

211
00:10:10,880 --> 00:10:12,810
I don't want to interfere with him.

212
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:15,490
Let him choose for himself.

213
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:18,640
I can't stand it anymore. I'll talk to him.

214
00:10:18,640 --> 00:10:19,320
Yan Xue.

215
00:10:19,800 --> 00:10:22,000
This is Xiaocen and Xu Xiao's own business.

216
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:23,000
Don't interfere.

217
00:10:24,640 --> 00:10:25,200
Fine.

218
00:10:27,480 --> 00:10:28,200
Xiaocen,

219
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:31,520
if Xu Xiao really decides

220
00:10:31,640 --> 00:10:32,800
to study abroad,

221
00:10:34,080 --> 00:10:35,940
have you thought about what to do?

222
00:10:42,160 --> 00:10:43,400
How's the work going?

223
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:48,280
The restoration work is going pretty well.

224
00:10:48,400 --> 00:10:49,440
Mr. Zeng also said

225
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:51,970
he would give me more restoration work later.

226
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:54,780
Congratulations.

227
00:10:55,040 --> 00:10:56,960
The restoration environment here is great.

228
00:10:56,960 --> 00:10:58,760
And the schools here in Malaysia

229
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,160
have specially set up

230
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:02,040
a dedicated X-ray spectrometer.

231
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:05,200
It can test the age and composition

232
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,130
of the ceramics.

233
00:11:06,400 --> 00:11:08,880
I've only seen it in the provincial museum before.

234
00:11:08,880 --> 00:11:10,010
Do you want to see it?

235
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:12,040
I'll show it to you on video later.

236
00:11:12,040 --> 00:11:13,240
I don't want to see it.

237
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:14,880
You don't need to show me.

238
00:11:17,720 --> 00:11:18,520
What's wrong?

239
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:20,530
Nothing.

240
00:11:22,040 --> 00:11:23,770
I know you're doing well there.

241
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:26,370
And I know it's great there.

242
00:11:30,720 --> 00:11:32,360
Then continue with your restoration.

243
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:33,220
I'm hanging up.

244
00:11:33,640 --> 00:11:35,370
But we haven't talked for long.

245
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:48,480
Xiaocen, come here.

246
00:11:49,280 --> 00:11:51,280
Try the persimmon. It's very sweet.

247
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:55,210
What's wrong, Xiaocen?

248
00:11:55,320 --> 00:11:57,250
Tell me if you have any grievances.

249
00:12:03,480 --> 00:12:04,080
Xiaocen,

250
00:12:04,720 --> 00:12:06,250
what are your thoughts now?

251
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:09,460
If he has already made up his mind,

252
00:12:10,160 --> 00:12:11,220
I will support him.

253
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:16,280
Xiaocen,

254
00:12:16,880 --> 00:12:18,560
you are a very kind girl

255
00:12:19,360 --> 00:12:21,290
and always considerate of others.

256
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:23,600
But you should also think for yourself.

257
00:12:24,080 --> 00:12:26,680
You have the right to pursue your own happiness

258
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:28,520
and fight for what you want.

259
00:12:32,720 --> 00:12:34,920
I'm afraid he'll think I'm too selfish.

260
00:12:36,440 --> 00:12:38,480
Maybe he has already made his decision.

261
00:12:38,480 --> 00:12:39,940
Overthinking is useless.

262
00:12:41,440 --> 00:12:43,160
If you don't say some things out loud,

263
00:12:43,160 --> 00:12:44,890
you will never know the answer.

264
00:12:45,480 --> 00:12:47,480
You must be brave to speak your mind.

265
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:49,770
Don't be afraid of being rejected.

266
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:52,860
At least you won't regret it if you tried.

267
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:56,920
I just don't know how to say it.

268
00:13:01,160 --> 00:13:03,120
If you really care about him

269
00:13:03,760 --> 00:13:05,240
and don't want him to leave you,

270
00:13:05,240 --> 00:13:06,640
then you should tell him.

271
00:13:07,160 --> 00:13:08,200
Your relationship

272
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:09,720
is worth trying for once.

273
00:13:10,440 --> 00:13:12,440
Don't let yourself regret it later.

274
00:13:12,520 --> 00:13:13,480
Aunt.

275
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:16,160
When I was young,

276
00:13:16,160 --> 00:13:17,400
I was reckless for love

277
00:13:17,400 --> 00:13:19,000
and did a lot of silly things.

278
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:21,480
Now it seems

279
00:13:22,520 --> 00:13:23,800
that my love was misplaced.

280
00:13:23,800 --> 00:13:24,800
But I don't regret

281
00:13:25,360 --> 00:13:26,240
any choice I made at that time.

282
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:27,840
Young people should be brave

283
00:13:29,320 --> 00:13:31,400
and leave no regrets for themselves.

284
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:33,280
Xiaocen,

285
00:13:40,040 --> 00:13:40,970
what is the thing

286
00:13:41,480 --> 00:13:43,480
you want to do most

287
00:13:43,720 --> 00:13:45,000
